Hello,

when different issues are open in multiple browser tabs, attempting to complete a _Move Issue Operation_ will only succeed for one of them, while for the other it will silently fail (the issues won't be actually moved at all).

This unexpected behavior is due to storing the MoveIssueBean in the _session_, which is shared within a single browser instance, under an unique key.
{code:java}
public MoveIssueBean getMoveIssueBean()
    {
        return (MoveIssueBean) ActionContext.getSession().get(SessionKeys.MOVEISSUEBEAN);
    }
{code}

Would it be possible to change this behavior so that multiple _Moves_ can be concurrently "in flight"?


Best Regards,
Edoardo

